The Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation (NNPC) said it generated N2.197trillion from the sale of petrol between December 2019 and December 2020. In the period under review, the Group General Manager, Group Public Affairs Division, Dr. Kennie Obateru, in a statement, said NNPC recorded an increase of 80.12 per cent in trading surplus for December 2020, which stands at ₦24.19billion compared to the ₦13.43billion surplus recorded in November 2020. Trading surplus or trading deficit is derived after deduction of the expenditure profile from the revenue in the period under review. According to the report, the operating revenue of the NNPC Group in December 2020 as compared to November 2020 increased by 33.44 per cent or N137.00billion to stand at N546.65billion. It also said expenditure for the month increased by 27.54 per cent or N112.81billion to stand at N522.47billion. The statement noted the December 2020, expenditure as a proportion of revenue is 0.96 per cent as against 0.97 per cent in November 2020. The report indicated the 80.12 per cent increase is due mainly to the significant rise in the profit of NNPC’s flagship upstream entity, the Nigerian Petroleum Development Company (NPDC) amid improved market fundamentals and strong global demand for crude oil. The Nation The Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation said on Sunday that the total sale of petroleum products for the period November 2019 to November 2020 stood at 17.031 billion litres, with petrol accounting for 16.911 billion litres or 99.29 per cent. The Petroleum Products Marketing Company is principally engaged in the supply… In "Business" The Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation (NNPC) has recorded an encouraging 43 per cent drop in cases of willful damage of its oil pipeline infrastructure by suspected oil thieves in May, 2020.The corporation, in a release by its Group General Manager, Group Public Affairs Division, Dr. Kennie Obateru, explained that details… In "News" By Edith Ike-Eboh Abuja,